Reasoning: The paper discusses decoding algorithms for Reed-Solomon codes, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT). The Berlekamp-Massey algorithm and the Sugiyama et al. adaptation of the Euclidean algorithm are both algorithms used in data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses a new way to use the Euclidean algorithm, which is a common algorithm in computational complexity (cs.CC) and signal processing (cs.SI).
